<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Adam Sandler enjoyed some quality time with his daughter Sunny on Monday in Los Angeles.</p>

<p>The 53-year-old actor wore a loose blue T-shirt and baggy blue shorts while grabbing lunch in the Pacific Palisades area during the Labor Day holiday.</p>

<p>He completed his casual outfit with white socks and black sneakers.</p>

<p>Doting dad: Adam Sandler enjoyed some quality time with his daughter Sunny on Monday in Los Angeles during the Labor Day holiday</p>

<p>Adam also covered his mouth and nose with a black face mask amid the coronavirus pandemic.</p>

<p>Sunny, 11, accompanied her father on a scooter while wearing a grey hoodie and black leggings.</p>

<p>She also covered up with a face mask for their Labor Day outing.</p>

<p>Adam and wife Jackie, 45, also have 14-year-old daughter Sadie together.</p>

<p>Casual style: The 53-year-old actor wore a loose blue T-shirt and baggy blue shorts while grabbing lunch in the Pacific Palisades area with his daughter</p>

<p>Jackie and Adam met in 1998 on the set of Big Daddy and married five years later in Malibu at the oceanfront property of the late Dick Clark.</p>

<p>Adam can next be seen in the Netflix comedy Hubie Halloween that he also co-wrote and co-produced.</p>

<p>The film takes place in Salem, Massachusetts and follows eccentric Hubie DuBois, played by Adam, as he finds himself at the center of a murder case on Halloween night.</p>

<p>Going strong: Jackie and Adam, shown in February in Beverly Hills, California, met in 1998 on the set of Big Daddy and married five years later in Malibu</p>

<p>The movie was principally filmed last year, but shooting was not yet complete when production was halted due to the coronavirus pandemic.</p>

<p>Netflix has not yet announced a release date for Hubie Halloween.</p>

<p>The film also features Kevin James, Julie Bowen, Maya Rudolph, Ray Liotta, Steve Buscemi, Rob Schneider, Kenan Thompson, Tim Meadows and Colin Quinn.</p>

<p>Family portrait: Jackie, Sadie, Sunny and Adam are shown in September 2019 in Los Angeles</p>
